We should be working on a global scale, educating and building partnerships with governments and businesses in countries around the world. Crypto has the potential to be a powerful tool for financial inclusion and to improve the lives of people in every corner of the world.
I believe that if 7.7 billion people on Earth adopt crypto as legal tender, the 300 million people in the US will eventually follow suit.

As we work towards the adoption of #TRX as legal tender, let's not be too US-centric. US🇺🇸 regulation is important, but we should focus on the 8 billion people on Earth. The US is just one country, and while it may be a major player in the crypto world, it's not the only one.

This is a ambitious goal, but I am confident that with hard work and dedication, we can make it a reality.

1⃣最让我引以为傲的无疑是几次足以载入NFT发展史册的投资。我个人在NFT领域一直十分活跃，大手笔购入了许多NFT。从年初2000万美元拍下毕加索名作，到7800余万美元拍下《鼻子》，再到1500万美元买下无聊猿头像。这些投资的价值是多维度的，以这种方式支持NFT，是我作为行业引领者之一应有的态度与远见。

“It is certain that in specific historical periods and systems, people’s self-inflated persuasive power and impetuosity are major causes of crises. A relevant question thus arises: Does the rational actor hypothesis of economics hold true forever?”

“As described by the US economist John Galbraith, when the economy is overheated, no one doubts the continued inflation of the bubble. Instead of accepting reasons that cool their minds, people seek reasons that justify their blind adventures.”

“With a general impulsive mindset and encouraged by an easy monetary environment and financial innovations centered on leveraging up, people rushed into highly risky speculative activities with borrowed money, contributing to enormous asset bubbles.”

“People would easily buy various stories of speculative miracles, and their avarice and forgetfulness ballooned to an unheard-of degree. Few people could resist the temptation of indus- trial bubbles.”

“The epic industrial growth and gargantuan gaps in incomes and distributions before the two crises distorted public psychology in the capitalist world. A yearning to change their social status had spurred people to dream about making huge fortunes overnight. “
